UMUAHIA – Executive Secretary of Abia State Health Primary Agency, Dr. Chinagorom Adindu has raised an alarming sharp increase in Diabetes-related ailments among residents of the State and cautioned against consumption of processed foods and the high percentage of Sugar. Speaking to Daily Independent at a One Day Free Diabetes, Screening Test, Counseling and Free Drugs organized by Barrister Randy Obinna Ukawoke for People of Umuahia South Council Area at the Council Headquarter, Apumiri Ubakala, weekend further observed that people no longer watch what they consume. He said the only way to combat the Life-threatening ailment is for people to go for Diabetes Screening tests and regular medication, saying it is the only measure to reduce the high level of mortality rate among patients “There are ways we can prevent diabetes it is by proper nutrition and watching what we eat” On what the State Government has done to sensitize the people, especially in the rural areas, the State Primary Health Care Agency, Dr. Adindu said the State has procured kits to test Sugar Level which he said could be accessed at the various Health Centres in the State. Earlier in his remarks, the organizer of the Health Outreach programme and Founder of Obinnwanne Foundation, Chief Randy Ukawoke recalled that his decision to embark on the health outreach programme, especially on Diabetes, was a result of the death of two prominent people in life to Diabetes.